abstract: ST. JOHN'S, N.F., May 30. -- The French mission ship St. Pierre, 550 tons, bound from St. Pierre for the Grand Banks, to work among the French fishing fleet engaged there, drove ashore at midnight last night on Cape St. Marys and became a total loss. Her officers and men escaped and were landed at Placentia by a fishing boat, which picked them up.
